s study are equally important: are we prepared today for the catastrophes that climate change could bring tomorrow? At half the original length, this user-friendly abridgment is ideal for students and general readers seeking a rapid handle on the key issues.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aCivil WarxHistoryy17th century. 0aClimatic changesxHistoryy17th century. 0aClimatic changesxSocial aspectsxHistoryy17th century. 0aDisastersxHistoryy17th century. 0aHistory, Moderny17th century. 0aHistory, Modern. 0aHuman ecologyxHistoryy17th century. 0aMilitary historyy17th century. 0aMilitary history, Moderny17th century. 0aNatural disastersxHistoryy17th century. 0aRevolutionsxHistoryy17th century. 7aHISTORY / World.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311063898140uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030022635540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300226355423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300226355/original  a978-3-11-063898-1  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles